.TH WHOHAMI 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
whohami \- display the DigiHub identity currently installed on this system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B whohami
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B whohami
reads
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
and prints a formatted summary of the installed callsign, license
class/status/expiry, name, address, Maidenhead grid, and coordinates.
.PP
License class and status codes are expanded to their full names (e.g.
"G" becomes "General", "A" becomes "Active") for display.
.PP
This is a read\-only, informational command. To change any of this
information, use
.BR dhedit (1).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show the currently installed identity:
.B whohami
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
Source of all displayed information.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Displayed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
The shared UI library could not be loaded, or
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
does not exist or is not readable (run
.B install.sh
first).
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR dhedit (1),
.BR sysinfo (1)
